posts.title: Does my friend sound toxic?
posts.text:
Firstly, I'm a pretty liberal person, but I've recently started hanging out with someone who is super far left. She's very involved politically and never misses a protest. We get along well, but there's parts of her personality that drive me nuts.
She's kind of like the moral police. Nobody is allowed to tell politically incorrect jokes, no one can speak out of term, and she hates when people disagree. Today, a mutual friend of ours said she was attracted to black men. This was the conversation between this friend and our mutual friend that started off about the mutual's sister saying she'd never date a black guy.
"Yeah, my sister is ridiculous. I'm really attracted to black men."
"You shouldn't fetishize black men."
"I don't, I'm just stating I'm objectively attracted to them even though my sister says she's not."
"Well, you should like people for who they are."
"I do! That's not the only thing I look for in someone. I'm allowed to find people attractive."
sighs "Just stop, you don't get it"
Another time, we were catching up. I asked if she was dating anyone (just making conversation), and she blew up at me saying "Why does it always have to be about men! Why do I have to be with someone?"
I didn't even know what to say. There have been so many of these little instances to count. The dumbest part is that she rakes men over the coals all the time, and that makes her seem like a giant hypocrite. She even wears this shirt around that says "MEN AREN'T FUNNY" and everyone gives her weird looks. It's so embarrassing.
Has anyone else had experience with someone like this? Would she qualify as a toxic friend?

posts.text:
Topolánka bych podpořil, říká Marek Benda Publikováno: 07.11.2017 08:30 Audio záznam Audio není možné přehrát! Omlouváme se. Tři otázky na tělo položila v úterý ráno Zuzana Bubílková bývalému studentskému vůdci a nejdéle sloužícímu poslanci za ODS, Marku Bendovi. 
Dobré ráno, pane Bendo. Po revoluci ODS tvrdila, že komunisté zaniknou přirozenou cestou. Proč jsou pořád v parlamentu? 
Tak nezanikli, bohužel. I když po těchto volbách jsou mimořádně oslabeni. Já myslím, že se pomalu propadají do zapomnění. Je zjevné, že jak ubíhá čas, tak se na hrůzy komunismu zapomíná a stále jsou pro některé části společnosti přitažliví. 
Teď měli komunisté jen necelých 8%. Byl to výkyv, nebo trend? 
To samozřejmě uvidíme. Myslím, že tentokrát je mimořádně zdecimovalo hnutí Andreje Babiše ANO, které vybralo hlasy úplně všem. Od komunistů až po pravý střed. Jestli to bude dlouhodobější trend, bylo by to samozřejmě dobře - kdyby komunisté přestali tady ty hlasy brát. 
Kdyby hrozilo, že se SPD půjdou komunisté do vlády - čímž odblokují současnou situaci - co byste v ODS udělali? 
Tak tohle je otázka pro vítěze voleb, jestli je připraven s nimi jít do vlády. ODS rozhodně nechce zachraňovat zemi za cenu toho, že se sama zničí, nebo že začne kolaborovat s Andrejem Babišem. Jestli si myslíme, že Andrej Babiš není komunista… Tak přece v té straně byl taky, velmi pravděpodobně byl agentem Státní bezpečnosti. To znamená, že je to stále stejná líheň a my se s ním opravdu zaplétat nebudeme. 
Retro u části společnosti frčí. Retro premiér za ODS Topolánek se chce ucházet o post prezidenta. Podpoříte ho? 
Tak, já osobně bych samozřejmě Mirka Topolánka podpořil. Protože myslím, že v tom výběru kandidátů, který se nabízí, je to člověk, který má politickou zkušenost. Byl předsedou vlády, byl předsedou Evropské rady. Myslím, že má za sebou poměrně hodně práce.

posts.author: domani spero
posts.title: @StateDept Redesign Briefing Presents Five “Guiding Beliefs” and Five “Key Outcomes” #OMG
posts.text:
Follow @Diplopundit 

The State Department is still in the midst of its redesign exercise . We understand that a couple of weeks ago, a State Department top official did a redesign presentation to ranking officials of the agency. This must be part of Phase 3 of the redesign efforts to communicate the plan to the employees and external stakeholders. This phase also includes the implementation of “functional projects” that reportedly supports the “Comprehensive Redesign” (we don’t yet know what are those projects, but we’ve been hearing about purported “quick wins”). Further, this phase reportedly includes the “development of an atmosphere of culture change.” We’re still waiting to learn how they’re gonna do cultural change in Foggy Bottom. 
(See Why Tillerson Not Sullivan Needs the Town Hall: Morale Is Bad, “S” is Accountable) 
The presentation notes first that “Diplomacy and development will become even more important as global power dynamics continue to change.” (Wait — a newbie at the State Department told diplomats and development professionals with decades of experience that diplomacy and development will become even more important even as the agency is planning to slash its funding and staff?). 
Did anyone laugh out loud during the presentation? 
The presentation then explains the State Department and USAID’s “Guiding Beliefs” for the Tillerson redesign. There are reportedly five of these beliefs: 
➨ 1. We will each need to communicate directly and continually engage with our domestic and global stakeholders regarding our purposes, missions, ambitions, and achievements. 
➨ 2. We will each need the agility to adopt state-of-the-art information technologies and to adapt to rapidly changing technological advancements that are driving broader changes in the world. 
➨ 3. We will each need to modernize our workforce systems (including recruitment, training, and performance management to maintain passionate, top-quality, and more agile workforces). 
➨ 4. Our respective decision-making will need to take advantage of advancements in knowledge management and in data collection, analytics, and visualization. 
➨ 5. We will need to focus on our respective comparative advantages as we address threats and leverage opportunities posed by the growing power and influence of emerging states, non-state actors, civil society, the private sector, and individuals. 
All nice words. And 1) they can start communicating with their employees starting with S, the chief sponsor of this change; 2) money, money, money ; 3) uh-oh; 4) darnit, darnit, science! and 5) boo! 
The second presentation point notes that “global competition for economic, financial, natural, human, and technological resources, and changes in society and social structures (brought on by migration, climate change, large scale unemployment, social isolation, wealth disparities, and similar shifts) will create opportunities for inter- and intra-state conflict and/or cooperation.” 
No. Kidding. Is this Foggy Bottom’s kindergarten class? 
And third, that “growing reliance on data and technology will increase vulnerabilities at the micro and macro levels, requiring new approaches to risk mitigation at all levels of government and among all elements of society both in the United States and abroad.” 
Who. Knew? 
The presentation also talks about the five key outcomes namely: effective and strategic global leadership maximizing the impact of foreign assistance mission-driven, high performing, agile workforce nimble and data informed decision making mission enabling, world-class infrastructure support 
Given that the State Department has now communicated the U.S. intent to withdraw from the Paris Agreement , our most favorite part in this list of outcomes gotta be “data informed decision making.” 
The presentation also talks about “tranche goals” and “five outcome goals”— oops! Don’t look now! We’ve gone mighty dizzy. 
But holy moly guacamole! Which intern should be sent to the Republic of Nambia for this BS? #

thread.title_full: Jamal retracts statement against Zuraida, the two settle defamation case - Nation | The Star Online

posts.author: thestar.com.my
posts.title: Jamal retracts statement against Zuraida, the two settle defamation case
posts.text:
KUALA LUMPUR: A defamation suit filed by Ampang MP Zuraida Kamaruddin against Red Shirts leader Datuk Seri Jamal Md Yunos (pic) for associating her with his bloodied nose incident, has been resolved via mediation.
The matter was settled after Jamal retracted his remark against Zuraida, made at Ampang Point Mall in November last year.
He read out the consent judgment in court before Justice S. Nantha Balan Tuesday.
Jamal, the defendant, said he had used the words in anger against Zuraida and regretted it.
"I would like to retract the words uttered during a tense situation against YB Zuraida Kamaruddin at Ampang Point Mall over the publication on Nov 13, last year as stated in the third paragraph of the statement of claim dated Nov 17," he said.
Jamal also promised not to repeat any statement relating to the incident against the plaintiff.
Justice Nantha Balan later recorded the consent judgement and thanked all parties for being able to settle the suit via mediation without a full trial.
In her statement of claim, Zuraida alleged that the Sungai Besar Umno division chief had falsely and maliciously uttered and published the defamatory words to the media and the public on Nov 13.
The plaintiff said that Jamal knew the words would be widely published and spread via online news portals, print and electronic media.
The words, she said, were meant that she had directed her party members or her friends to commit a crime resulting in the injuries; that she was violent or a person who was prepared to commit or provoke the act of physical violence; that she was not fit to become an MP and that she was a criminal.
She had sought aggravated and general damages; an injunction to refrain Jamal or his agents from further publishing the defamatory words orally or via print media or the Internet as well as costs.
Jamal was involved in a fracas between the Red Shirts group and the police at Ampang Point Mall on Nov 13, 2016.
He initially claimed that a policeman punched him, but later claimed that it was Zuraida's men who had left him with a bloodied nose.

posts.title: 尤纳斯谈战新疆：重要的是球员能不能硬起来_CBA_新浪竞技风暴_新浪网
posts.text:
尤纳斯 北京时间11月7日，上赛季的总决赛对手新疆广东新赛季首次相遇。广东队主教练尤纳斯表示，重要的是队员能不能硬起来。而广东的优势在三秒区，新疆在外线，谁能发挥出来，谁就能获胜。
尤纳斯深知这场比赛对于媒体的意义，但在他看来这仍旧是一场普通的比赛，“最好的情况是，我们每一场比赛都不需要动员，因为我们是职业球员，每一场比赛都要有战斗的欲望。但今天的对手是上赛季总决赛的对手，还是有些不一样。但从另一方面来说，这仅仅是一场普通的常规赛而已。”
有记者说明觉得今天广东队的备战时间很长，但尤纳斯却不认同，“我们准备的方式都一样，对每场比赛都会准备得很想尽，看很多对手的录像，进行针对性的分析。但是今天最重要的是，我们的球员能不能硬起来。三秒区内是我们的强项，而对手的优势则在于外线，我们会看谁能够更好地发挥自己的优势。”
亚当斯当然是绕不开的话题，“亚当斯是个很好的得分手，但新疆不仅仅有他一个得分手，只是他是所有进攻的发起者。今天的比赛，将是我们年轻后卫很好的一堂课。对于年轻球员来说，能够和这样的球员对位是个很好的机会，我想胡明轩和赵睿能展示给我看，他们能防住这样优秀的球员。”
赵睿开赛以来表现不错，尤纳斯说到他，也给予了很高的评价，“最重要的是我很信任他（赵睿），他打得很不错，未来他还能又怎样的提升，取决于他自己。”
（晨曦）
